race.comment: ZAYA (6) has been racing well without winning, placing all three runs back here. Peaking now and should prove very tough to stop. BOOM CRUSHER (3) arrived just in time to make a winning return at Rockhampton and finally shed his maiden tag. Is sure to have come on with that run under his belt and is a big chance to make it two on the bounce. HE'S THE ONE (4) settled well back last time out and never threatened at Doomben but his prior form stacks right up. Faces a much more suitable assignment this time and gets his chance to break a long run of outs. MELO MELO KAVA (2) backs up quickly after racing on speed and finishing second over 1400m at Rockhampton. Drops back in trip and is among the chances. SPRING'S GIFT (7) was a barnstorming winner two back to get off the mark, then followed it up with a strong chasing effort at Townsville. Deserves consideration.
